Learn about Indian Weddings with me 
•M E H N D I •
Mehndi (also known as henna) is a decorative paste traditionally representing the holy bond of matrimony. Applying the paste to the bride’s hands and feet is considered a shagun (sign of good luck) it is said to aid fertility, ward off evil, and attract positive energy! 
The grooms name is hidden in the brides hand, and it is said to be even more good luck if the groom finds it on the wedding night! 

According to different legends, the darker the mendhi, the more 1) your mother in law loves you 2) the more your husband loves you ♥️ either way, I’m in luck, mine came out so dark!!!! 

I’ve always LOVED mehndi and have been looking forward to this my whole life!!

5 HOT TIPS to RAISE the BAR:

1: Give yourself permission to GO for GOOD ENOUGH. DONE is better than perfect. If you’ve been and A+ student I want you to let go of that mindset and know that B- is “GOOD ENOUGH” because is means your taking action instead of standing still. SMALL wins over Big wins alllll day baby.

2. Strive for excellence, NOT PERFECTION. Our best is good enough. Embrace your failures and KEEP going!

3. Break up with your addiction to comparing yourself to others. Start creating your own life & business instead of sitting back constantly consuming what is going on is other people’s lives- this is only holding you back! (I give you permission to UNFOLLOW any account that is currently distracting you. Keep in mind- you might think they’re inspiring you, but if you’re spending more time watching their life than enjoying your OWN “UNFOLLOW” or mute). This doesn’t make you a mean person & you can still love from afar ♥️

4. Consider the BEST/WORST/REAL scenarios. Are you making things worse then they are? What are your stories. Are you telling yourself encouraging stories or disempowering ones? You can change these, but cha gotta get real w. YOU!

5. Put time on your side. Break down what you need to do. Get specific. Set ACHIEVABLE goals, especially if you’re just getting started! Set timers on your phone for 25min working sessions & focus on ONE task at a time. Turn off notifications!

An overwhelmed + confused mind does nothing.

NO one on this planet is perfect, so it’s time to let go of the desire to be perfect that is only holding you back.

It’s more fun being the real-you anyways, without the perfectionist mask on.
.
.
.

Prioritizing yourself is crucial for maintaining a healthy balance in your life. Remember, taking care of yourself is not selfish, it’s necessary. Here are a few tips to help you prioritize yourself:

Set boundaries: Learn to say no to things that don’t align with your values or goals.
Make time for yourself: Schedule time for activities that bring you joy and relaxation.
Speak kindly to yourself: Practice self-compassion and avoid self-criticism.
Take care of your physical and mental health: Eating well, exercising, and getting enough sleep are important for overall well-being.
Don’t feel guilty: Remember, prioritizing yourself is necessary for being able to give to others and be present in your relationships.

#SelfCareFirst #SetBoundaries #MeTimeMatters #SelfCompassion #WellnessPriorities #PrioritizeYou #GuiltFreeSelfCare #HealthyBalance #SayNoToWhatDoesntServeYou #MindBodyWellness #SelfLoveJourney

Focus on delivering value: Always prioritize delivering value to your customers, whether it’s through the quality of your products or the level of service you provide. This will not only help you retain existing customers, but it will also attract new ones.

Invest in your personal brand: Your personal brand is what sets you apart from your competitors, so make sure to put effort into building and promoting it. This can include things like creating a strong online presence, speaking at events, and consistently putting out quality content.

Embrace change and experimentation: The business world is constantly evolving, so it’s important to be flexible and open to trying new things. Experiment with new marketing strategies, embrace technology, and always be willing to pivot and make changes as needed. The businesses that are able to adapt and evolve are the ones that will thrive in the long run.

Not having a clear vision
One of the biggest mistakes that entrepreneurs make is diving headfirst into their businesses without defining their vision. It’s essential to have a clear understanding of where you want your business to go and how you plan to get there. Take the time to define your goals, target audience, and marketing strategies. Develop a comprehensive business plan that outlines your objectives, budget, and timeline for achieving your goals. Regularly review and update your plan as your business evolves to ensure that you’re on the right track.

Ignoring customer feedback
Your customers are the backbone of your business, and their feedback is crucial to your success. One of the most common mistakes entrepreneurs make is ignoring customer feedback or not actively seeking it out. Create channels for your customers to provide feedback through surveys, reviews, or social media. When you receive feedback, take it seriously and make changes accordingly. Your customers will appreciate it, and your business will benefit in the long run.

Relying solely on passion
Many entrepreneurs believe the mantra, “do what you love, and the money will come.” However, passion alone is not enough to succeed in business. Running a business comes with daily frustrations, employee issues, and a market that doesn’t always support your product or service. While passion is a helpful ingredient, it must be matched with equal parts of practicality, focus, hard work, and business smarts. As an entrepreneur, your responsibility is not to do one task – it’s to run a business. If you’re excited about wearing multiple hats and want to tackle the challenge of managing all aspects of an operation, you’re headed in the right direction.

Listen up! …literally 
Communication is a two-way street, and it’s not just about what we say, but also about how we say it and to whom we say it.

So many people make the mistake of assuming that others think and feel the same way they do. They fail to take the time to understand their audience’s perspectives, values, and beliefs. Without this understanding, it’s difficult to tailor our communication to resonate with our audience, and we may end up speaking in a completely different  language that is not understood or relevant to them.

To communicate effectively, we need to take the time to understand our audience and tailor our message accordingly. We need to listen actively and empathetically to their needs, concerns, and interests, and then craft our message in a way that speaks to them. This requires us to put our egos aside, be open-minded, and genuinely interested in connecting with others.

A healthy dupe of snickers 🍫 

Super easy 6 ingredient dessert thank took about 15 min to make! 
It turned out even more delicious than I expected! 
& turned into the perfect hiking snack! 
Anyone want to try some? 

Ingredients: 
2 cups Pitted dates 
1 cup Almonds 
2 Tbsp Almond butter 
2 Tbsp Maple syrup 
1 cup Dark chocolate 
Crushed peanuts 

1. In a food processor, blend the dates and almonds for the base until they form a sticky mixture.

2 Add almond butter and pulse until well combined.

3. Press the base mixture into a lined baking dish.

4. In the same food processor, blend dates, almond butter, and maple syrup until it forms a caramel-like consistency.

5. Spread the caramel layer over the base in the baking dish.

6. Melt dark chocolate chips in a microwave or over a double boiler.

7. Pour the melted chocolate over the caramel layer and spread it evenly.

8 Optional: Sprinkle crushed peanuts over the chocolate layer.

9 Place the dish in the refrigerator for about 1-2 hours until it firms up.

10. Once firm, cut into bars

However with a fun weekend filled with celebrating people we love, I do everything I can to make sure I am present in the moment. 
Here are some things I do to make sure I take care of myself 
• my morning rituals: meditation, hydrate, healthy breakfast and some type of movement 
• carry my water bottle … it’s a hot girl hydrated summer
• take snacks with me (as a vegetarian I am extra cautious of bringing snacks with protein because typically party options don’t have any)
• communicate whatever I need to ahead of time so I can put my phone away during the event 
• take my liftoff & fat release with me so I can feel good with foods I don’t normally eat

Chocolate coconut bars 🥥 🍫 

Super easy 5 ingredient dessert! 
I love coconut & these taste way too good 🤤 

Ingredients: 
• 2 cups Unsweetened coconut flakes/shreds
• 1/4 cup coconut oil 
• 1/4 cup full fat canned coconut milk boz 
• dark or semi-sweet chocolate (i use dairy free)
• 1/4 cup raw honey or pure maple syrup

1. first, melt the coconut oil. 

2. next, make the coconut filling: 
add the shredded coconut, coconut milk, honey/ maple syrup, and melted coconut oil  to a food processor and process for about a minute, scraping down the sides as needed. 

3. once smooth, add the coconut filling to an 8x5 loaf pan lined with parchment paper and smooth it out. place in the freezer to harden for several hours.

1. once frozen, remove the coconut filling from the freezer and slice into 6 bars.

5. melt the chocolate in the microwave or on the stovetop (i recommend adding 1 tsp of coconut oil to the chocolate to help it melt smoothly and thin it out).

6. once melted, coat each coconut bar in melted chocolate and place on a tray lined with parchment paper. place in the fridge to harden for several hours.

We shared these with our family and they were gone within a day! Typical Indian family that loves coconut & chocolate lol

Crunchwrap (more) Supreme 
Taco Bell isn’t the healthiest but ngl their menu still shows up in my dreams!
So we made it healthy… and it tastes even better! 
Quick recipe- takes about 20 min

Crunchwrap (more) Supreme Recipe: 
Ingredients:
	•	4 tortillas (10-inch diameter)- I use grain free tortillas
	•	1 cup cooked black beans (can or from dry beans)
	•	1 cup cooked protein - I used veggie protein from trader joes
	•	Veggies (shredded lettuce, diced tomatoes, diced onion, diced bell peppers, jalapeños) 
	•	1/2 cup shredded cheese (e.g., vegan cheddar, mexican or mozzarella)
	•	2 tablespoons chopped fresh cilantro
	•	2 tablespoons olive oil (for cooking)
	•	Guacamole or salsa (for serving, optional)

Recipe:
1. Cook black beans (from dry beans or can - I cook it from soaked dry beans). Add the taco seasoning and any other seasonings you like (I add a little enchilada sauce) 
2. In a large skillet, heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil over medium heat.
3. Add diced onion and bell peppers to the skillet and sauté until softened, about 3-4 minutes.
4. Lay one whole wheat tortilla on a clean surface. Place a layer of the black bean in the center of the tortilla, leaving about an inch of space from the edges.
5. Top the mixture with veggies, shredded cheese,  and chopped fresh cilantro.
6. Carefully fold the edges of the tortilla towards the center, creating a hexagon shape and sealing the fillings inside.
7. In the same skillet, add the remaining tablespoon of olive oil over medium heat.
8. Place the filled tortilla in the skillet, seam side down, and cook for 2-3 minutes on each side until it becomes golden and crispy.
9. Repeat the process with the remaining tortillas and fillings.
10. Once all the Crunchwraps are cooked, cut them in half and serve with guacamole or salsa, if desired.

Ravi-makes-me-feel-so-good 🍝 

Invited the in-laws over and wanted to make a delicious dish that would also leave us feeling good afterwards! 
The pasta
* 1 cup of white flour
* 1 cup of semolina/suji
* 1 cup luke warm water
* 2 tsp olive oil
* A pinch of Salt

The filling
* 2 packets of mushrooms
* Italian seasoning
* Parmesan cheese (w/out rennet) 
* Fresh garlic
* Fresh serrano peppers 
* 2 tbsp margarine 

The Sauce
* ½ Cup ghee 
* 1 ½ Cups coconut heavy whipping cream alternative 
* 2 Tsp fresh Garlic
* ½ Tsp Italian seasoning 
* ½ Teaspoon salt
* ¼ Teaspoon pepper
* ¼ Crushed red pepper 
* 2 Cups grated Parmesan cheese (w/out rennet) 
* 2 tsp Chickpea flour + almond milk mixture

Recipe:
The pasta 
1. Combine flour, semolina, salt, olive oil and water together to make a semi stiff dough. 
2. Cover and place in fridge for 30-40 minutes
3. Knead the dough on a floured surface and cut in half.
4. Roll out each 1/2 of the dough separately or pass it through a pasta roller till it is about 2 cm thin.
5. Use a ravioli cutter (or a cup like I did) to create pasta circles 

Filling 
1. Sauté the mushrooms in margarine add all seasonings 
2. Mix in Parmesan cheese.
3. Place filling in circles from 1/2 the dough
4. Take pasta circles from the second half of the dough and cover the filled pasta
5. Use ravioli sealer (or your fingers) to seal the two circles together
6. Place the Ravioli in boiling water for a few minutes to cook

The Sauce
* Add the ghee and cream alternative to a large skillet.
* Simmer over low heat for 2 minutes.
* Whisk in chickpea flour & almond milk mixture 
* Whisk in the garlic, Italian seasoning, salt, pepper and red pepper for one minute.
* Whisk in the parmesan cheese until melted.
* Add cooked Ravioli 
* Serve immediately.

4 ingredient watermelon 🍉 sorbet 

Ingredients:
~ 4 cups cubed frozen watermelon
1/4 lime (I got one from the garden so it looks yellow)
1-2 tbsp maple syrup 
4 tbsp unsweetened coconut cream

Recipe: 
1. Cut your watermelon in cubes and freeze 4 cups overnight

2. Add watermelon + lime + maple syrup + coconut cream to high powered food processor (seriously my favorite kitchen appliance!! ) 

3. Blend on high for about 5 min (using a spatula scrape down the sides every so often) 

Optional garnish 🍃 mint from the garden!

Homemade Peppermint Bark, perfect holiday treat 

Ingredients:
12 ounces dark chocolate, chopped
12 ounces white chocolate, chopped
1/2 teaspoon peppermint extract
Crushed candy canes
Instructions:
Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
Melt dark chocolate and spread it on the parchment paper.
Place in the refrigerator until set.
Melt white chocolate, stir in peppermint extract, and spread over the dark che layer.
Sprinkle crushed candy canes on top.
Chill until set, then break into pieces.

The most perfect way to spend our 1st Anniversary ♥️ 

With our anniversary so close to the holidays, we decided to do a staycation. Thank you @ritzcarltonlagunaniguel for an incredible experience, the best place to intentionally reflect on our first year married (9th year together) & set some commitments for 2024 🥂 

Here are some questions we asked ourselves:
* How did we grow as a couple – emotionally, spiritually, or physically?
* What challenges or conflicts did we overcome and how did we grow as a result?
* What were some of our favorite moments or experiences?
* How did we fall more in love with each other this year?
* What were some ways that we felt loved and appreciated by each other?
* What did we do to serve the people we love? 
* How do you feel I best supported you? 
* What is one thing that stands out to you that I did that really says “I love you” without saying “I love you”?
* Where do you think I could show up as a better partner?
* What are you committed to doing for yourself everyday?
* How are we committed to having fun this year? 
* How will we challenge ourselves to grow this year? 
* What are our goals spiritually, mentally, emotionally, financially & physically? 

Send this to your partner 🫶🏽

Start with 1 goal. Start with doing it today 👏🏽

You’re more likely to stick to goals in 2024 if you start with 1 goal,  you make it easy to start and break it down into smaller steps. 

I used to make a list of so many goal, each adding so much to my day. Don’t get me wrong I would do whatever it took to get through the list but it didn’t have the impact on my life that I wanted. I was left tired, feeling wrong and focused more on checking the box than being present. 

Everything changed when I changed my mindset around a new years goals-  Instead of associating huge numbers like “I want to read 24 books”, try I’m reading today. 
Take everyday as it’s own and soon days will turn into books.

#5 will change your mind

1•The 3, 2, 1 Method: Prioritize your tasks daily by identifying 3. must-do tasks, 2 important tasks, and 1 task you’d like to do. This helps in focusing on what’s essential and managing your time effectively.

2• Don’t Rely on Motivation: Build routines and habits that keep you going even when motivation wanes. Consistency in your actions, regardless of how you feel, is key to discipline.

3•72-Hour Rule: When you come up with a new idea or goal, take the first step towards it within 72 hours. This helps in translating ideas into action before the initial excitement fades.

4• Use a Decision System: Make decisions based on long-term benefits rather than short-term gratification. Ask yourself, “What do I want most?” rather than “What do I want now?”

5•Ask Your Future Self: In difficult situations, think about what your future self would do. This perspective can guide you to make choices that align with your long-term goals and values.

6•Set Clear Boundaries: Define what is acceptable and what isn’t in both your personal and professional life. Stick to these boundaries to maintain focus and avoid distractions.

7• Practice Self-Reflection: Regularly take time to reflect on your actions, progress, and areas for improvement. Self-reflection fosters self-awareness and helps you stay aligned with your goals.

These rules, when practiced consistently, can significantly enhance your discipline and overall effectiveness in life.
